The paper deals with a multi-modal neural machine translation model that incorporates spatial visual features obtained using pre-trained convolutional neural networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. However, the model also uses attention mechanisms to generate words in the target language, which is a common technique in Natural Language Processing (NLP) research. Therefore, the paper could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper reports state-of-the-art results on the Multi30k dataset, which is a benchmark for machine translation research. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
